All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AddEvent
AddEvent Activity for creating new events within the Matata application.
AddEventUnitTest
Runs tests using the Robolectric test framework for Android.
Administrator
The Administrator class represents an administrator user within the Matata application.
AdminReportActivity
AdminReportActivity displays statistics and reports for events, users, and facilities.
AdminView
The AdminView class provides an admin dashboard for managing events, organizers, users, and facilities.
CancelledEntrant
Represents a cancelled entrant with their name and reason for cancellation.
CancelledEntrantAdapter
Adapter class for displaying a list of cancelled entrants in a RecyclerView.
CancelledEntrantAdapter.ViewHolder
 
ClearPendingListFragment
ClearPendingListFragment class is a DialogFragment that provides a dialog prompt to the user, asking if they want to cancel all entrants who haven't accepted the invitation yet.
ConfirmationFragment
ConfirmationFragment class is a DialogFragment that provides a dialog prompt to the user, asking if they want to discard their unsaved changes and go back.
DatePickerFragment
DatePickerFragment is a DialogFragment that displays a date picker dialog to allow users to select a date.
DatePickerListener
DatePickerListener is an interface that provides a callback for handling date selections in the DatePickerFragment.
EditEvent
EditEvent activity allows users to edit details of an existing event.
Entrant
Entrant class represents an individual entrant with personal information including name, phone number, and email.
EntrantAdapter
EntrantAdapter is a RecyclerView adapter that binds a list of Entrant objects to views displayed in a RecyclerView.
EntrantAdapter.EntrantViewHolder
EntrantViewHolder is a view holder for Entrant items in the RecyclerView.
Event
Event class represents an event with details such as title, date, time, location, description, capacity, event ID, organizer ID, and a waitlist limit.
EventAdapter
EventAdapter is a RecyclerView adapter that binds a list of Event objects to views displayed in a RecyclerView.
EventAdapter.EventViewHolder
EventViewHolder holds references to the views for each Event item in the RecyclerView.
EventDetailActivity
EventDetailActivity displays the details of a selected event and allows users to join or withdraw from the event's waitlist.
EventDetailsFragment
A fragment that displays details of an event, including its title, date, time, and poster image.
EventDraw
The `EventDraw` activity allows event organizers to manage a draw process for selecting participants from a waitlist.
EventDrawTest
 
EventDrawUnitTest
 
EventHistory
The `EventHistory` activity displays a list of past events created by the user.
EventPagerAdapter
The `EventPagerAdapter` is an adapter for managing fragments in a ViewPager2.
ExampleInstrumentedTest
Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
ExampleUnitTest
Example local unit test, which will execute on the development machine (host).
ExploreEvents
The ExploreEvents class provides an interface for users to explore events on a map.
Facility
Facility class represents a facility with a name and description.
FacilityActivity
The FacilityActivity class allows users to view, edit, and save facility information, such as name, address, capacity, contact, email, owner, and profile picture.
FacilityFrozenDialogFragment
FacilityFrozenDialogFragment displays a dialog to notify the user that their facility is frozen.
FacilityInfoDialogFragment
FacilityInfoDialogFragment displays facility information in a dialog fragment.
FacilityPicActivity
FacilityPicActivity allows the user to view, select, upload, and delete a profile picture.
FrozenDialogFragment
FrozenDialogFragment displays a dialog informing the user that their account is frozen.
GeolocationService
The `GeolocationService` class represents a background service for handling geolocation-related tasks.
MainActivity
MainActivity serves as the central hub for the Matata app.
MainActivityTest
Runs instrumentation tests for the MainActivity using AndroidJUnit4.
ManageAllEventsActivity
The ManageAllEventsActivity class provides an interface for administrators to manage all events.
ManageAllFacilityActivity
The ManageAllFacilityActivity class provides an interface for administrators to manage all facilities.
ManageAllImagesActivity
The ManageAllImagesActivity class provides an interface for administrators to manage event posters.
ManageAllQRActivity
The ManageAllQRActivity class provides administrators with the ability to manage QR codes associated with events.
ManageAllUsersActivity
The ManageAllUsersActivity class provides an interface for administrators to manage all user profiles.
MapsActivity
The MapsActivity class is a fragment that integrates a Google Map.
Notification
The Notification class provides utility methods for managing and sending notifications.
NotificationTest
 
Organizer
Organizer class represents an organizer user with the ability to manage a facility.
ProfileActivity
ProfileActivity manages the user's profile, allowing them to edit personal information, view and update profile images, and manage facility data if they are an organizer.
ProfileActivityTest
Runs instrumentation tests for the ProfileActivity using AndroidJUnit4.
ProfilePicActivity
ProfilePicActivity allows the user to view, select, upload, and delete a profile picture.
ProfilePicActivityTest
Runs instrumentation tests for the ProfilePicActivity using AndroidJUnit4.
ProfileUnitTest
Runs tests using the Robolectric test framework for Android.
QR_camera
QR_camera class provides functionality for scanning QR codes using the device's camera.
QR_displayFragment
QR_displayFragment displays a QR code and provides an option to save it as a PNG file.
QR_displayListener
QR_displayListener is an interface for handling data read from a QR code.
Recycler_fragment
Recycler_fragment is a fragment used to display a list of events in a RecyclerView.
ScanQRUITest
 
ShadowSystemClock
Shadow implementation of the SystemClock class.
SignUpSheet
SignUpSheet class handles the creation of a sign-up form for event attendees.
SwipeView
The `SwipeView` class is a fragment that provides a swipe-based interface for viewing event details.
TimePickerFragment
TimePickerFragment displays a time picker dialog that allows users to select a time.
TimePickerListener
TimePickerListener is an interface that provides a callback for when a time is selected from a TimePickerFragment.
User
The User class serves as a superclass for user-related roles, such as Entrant and Organizer.
ViewEvent
The `ViewEvent` class represents the activity for viewing detailed information about an event.
ViewEventUnitTest
Runs tests for the ViewEvent activity using Robolectric.
